rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all amino acids. These are the organic compounds composed of amine (-NH2) and carboxylic acid (-COOH) functional groups, along with a side-chain specific to each amino acid. The key elements of an amino acid are carbon, hydrogen, oxygen, and nitrogen, though other elements are found in the side-chains of certain amino acids. About 500 amino acids are known.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Amino Acid

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.amino_acid to the standard three-letter codon sequences that code this amino acid in DNA.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: DNA Codons

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.amino_acid to the standard three-letter codon sequences that code this amino acid in RNA. RNA codons are essentially the same as DNA codons, except that T replaced by U.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: RNA Codons

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all body systems. A body system is a grouping of physiologically or anatomically related organs and parts. Examples include the digestive system and the nervous system.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Anatomical System

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The collection of types of animals. Included in this collection are entities like "Octopus", "Crab", and "Sheep". See also biology.organism for collections of individual organisms like "Gallant Fox" and "Smart Strike", both of which are individual horses.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Animal

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal to measurements of body length that specifically exclude one or more parts that would go into total length (for example, tail, limbs, stinger, head, antennae). Qualifiers should be used to indicate the specific exclusions (e.g. Without Tail).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Body Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal to its clutch size, an mso:measurement_unit.qualified_value. A clutch is the set of eggs laid, usually at a single time, by animals of this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Clutch size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal to the variety of the animal's coloration. Coloration is the general appearance of an animal resulting from the reflection or emission of light from its surfaces. Coloration can serve different purposes for the animal - camouflage, signalling, and mimicry, for example.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Animal Coloration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal to the length of time in a day that it sleeps.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Daily Sleep

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal to its diameter. This could be the diameter of a jellyfish's bell, but also the body diameter of a worm.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Diameter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: For a non-egg laying mammal, the period between fertilization and birth. Use only for mammals that do not lay eggs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gestation Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal to its height. Often height will be expressed in a way that excludes some part of the animal--for example, height to shoulder, or height minus a head crest. This should be indicated using a qualifier (for example, "At Shoulder"). Some kinds of animals (for example, snakes, fish, worms) are rarely described in terms of height. If only one measurement for the long dimension of an animal is given, use height if the animal walks upright or is otherwise vertically oriented, mso:biology.animal.length otherwise. When in doubt, use length.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Height

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal to the period, in days, of its hibernation, for those types that hibernate.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hibernation Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal to the length of the horns or antlers. Do not use for other protuberances of the head (like tentacles or ears).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Horn or Antler Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal to its long dimension for animals that do not typically walk or orient itself upright. If only one measurement for the long dimension of an animal is given, use mso:biology.animal.height if the animal walks upright or is otherwise vertically oriented, this property otherwise. When in doubt, use mso:biology.animal.length. Many animals have both a length and a height. See also mso:biology.animal.body_length to exclude one or more parts usually used in the total length.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal type to the length of time from birth to death in calendar years.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lifespan

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal type to the number of offspring birthed at one time. Do not use for pack size, troop size, or other groupings.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Litter size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal type to the mass in kilograms of its instances.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mass

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal to the name of its social grouping. For example, elephants are grouped into herds, and lions into prides. Social groupings are the communities of the predominately same animals that live and interact with each other.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Social Grouping

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal type to the speed of locomotion in km per hour for its instances.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Speed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal type to the tail length, in centimeters, of its instances. Do not use for anything but tails.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tail Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal type to the typical size of the territory over which the instances of the type ranges. Usually expressed in units squared (square feet, square miles, square meters) but sometimes in a linear measure from a point (e.g. "May range up to 10 miles from its den").
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Territory Extent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal to the span of the outstretched wings for instances of the type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wingspan

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all animal breeds. These are the special varieties of domesticated animals within a species that have a homogeneous appearance or behavior or have some other kind of characteristic that separate them from other members of the same species. Breeds are derived by selective breeding.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Animal Breed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal_breed to the average amount of cost for one of the breed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Average Cost

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an animal breed to its average height entity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breed Average Height

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an animal breed to its average weight entity.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breed Average Weight

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal_breed to the text description of the breed's body. This can include general shape and interesting anatomical features. See also mso:biology.animal_breed.coat_color and mso:biology.animal_breed.coat_description for specific coat properties.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Body Description

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal_breed to its typical or popular names for male individuals of the breed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Popular Boy Names

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal_breed to the mso:biology.domesticated_animal of which the breed is a type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breed of

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal_breed to the mso:biology.breed_registration relationship, which collects the data on the breed as recognize by various registries.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Registered with

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an animal breed to the color(s) of the breed's coat. Examples include descriptions like black, white and brindle and can include further descriptions like, with or without white markings.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Color

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an animal breed to the general description of the breed's coat.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal_breed to the mso:visual_art.color(s) typically found in this breed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Color

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal_breed to the mso:biology.pedigreed_animal(s) of this breed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Examples

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an animal breed to a description of the quantity of exercise needed by the breed. Examples include: low, medium, and high.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Exercise Requirement

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal_breed to a description of the breed's gait. Gait is the pattern of movement of the breed's limbs, and differing breeds have gaits specific to the breed based on anatomical differences.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gait

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal_breed to its typical or popular names for female individuals of the breed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Popular Girl Names

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an animal breed to the average life span for the breed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Life Span

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an animal breed to the average size of its litters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Litter Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an animal breed to a textual description of the amount of noise typically associated with the breed, e.g. the amount of barking in dogs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Noise Level

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:biology.animal_breed to the mso:biology.breed_origin, which is the origin for the given breed. Note mso:biology.breed_origin is deprecated, and the expected_type for this property should change to mso:location.location.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Place of Origin

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an animal breed to the cities in which the breed is popular as a pet.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Popular in Cities

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an animal breed to a description of the breed's general behavior. Examples include: sociable, patient, and alert.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Temperament

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal_breed to the general mso:biology.temperament(s) exhibited by instances of the breed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Temperament

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an animal breed to a description of the variety of the breed. With respect to dog breeds, examples include: hunting dog, hypoallergenic, apartment-friendly, light shedder, and family-friendly.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breed Variety

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration of categories of animal breeds that are commonly used but are not authoritative. With respect to dog breeds, examples include: hunting dog, hypoallergenic, apartment-friendly, light shedder, and family-friendly.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Animal Breed Variety

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of best guard breeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Best Guard

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value indicating that the breed requires grooming every day.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Daily Grooming

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value indicating that the breed is in general friendly with other dogs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dog Friendly

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of easy to train breeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Easy to Train

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of fluffy breeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fluffy

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of friendly breeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Friendly

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of giant breeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Giant Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value indicating that the breed is difficult to train.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hard to Train

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of kid-friendly breeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Kid Friendly

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of large breeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Large Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of medium breeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Medium Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value indicating that the breed requires grooming once a month.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Monthly Grooming

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value indicating that the breed does not shed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nonshedding

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value indicating that the breed is in general hostile or aggressive towards other dogs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Not Dog Friendly

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of unfriendly breeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Not Friendly

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of small breeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Small Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of smartest breeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Smartest Breeds

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of sporting dogs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sporting Dog

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of terrier dogs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Terrier Dog

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of toy breeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Toy Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of very friendly breeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Very Friendly

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration value indicating that the breed requires grooming once a week.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weekly Grooming

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Enumeration expressing the concept of working dogs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Working Dog

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that breeds animals, usually of a particular species, and raises the offspring until they can be sold.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Animal Breeder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that offers services of cleaning and brushing animals
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Animal Groomer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The primary entity representing the collection of individual animals. Instances of this collection would include "Gallant Fox", a thoroughbreed horse, and "Koko" the gorilla. Note this collection applies to individuals only, and not types of animals like "horse" and "octopus". For this primary entity, please see biology.animal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Animals

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal_organism to the coat color for the individual animal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an entity to its resting heart rate.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Resting Heart Rate
Animal ownership
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: Use common.ownership_relationship instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:common.ownership_relationship]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date this animal was acquired by this owner. If an owner possessed the animal multiple, non-consecutive, times, create separate instances for each.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use common.ownership_relationship.start_date instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:common.ownership_relationship.start_date]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The date after which this owner no longer possessed this animal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use common.ownership_relationship.end_date instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:common.ownership_relationship.end_date]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business whose activities are targeted at animals, particularly farm animals and pets.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Animal Service Provider

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An establishment that cares for injured or unwanted animals and eventually attempts to return them to the wild or find homes for them.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Animal Shelter

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data on an animal training relationship. Data in this type include the animal trained, the trainer, and the dates the relationship held.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Animal Training Relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.animal_training relationship to the mso:biology.animal_organism that was trained during the given time period.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Animal

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all biological functions. These are the reasons some object or process occurs in a system that evolved through a process of selection or natural selection. For example, the function of chlorophyll in a plant is to capture the energy of sunlight for photosynthesis.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Biological Function

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all biological pathways. These are the sets of actions among molecules in a cell that leads to a certain product or a change in a cell. For example, pathways can trigger the assembly of new molecules, turn genes on and off, or spur a cell to move.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Biological Pathway

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.biological_pathway to a mso:biology.gene that is involved in the pathway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gene

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The collection of all collections of blooms, also called flowers, which are the reproductive structure of flowering plants. This collection includes, for example, the collection of apple blossoms, the collection of rose flowers on rose bushes (both called roses), and the collection of daisy flowers found on daisy plants. This collection is specific to the plant part, as opposed to the other meaning of the term "flower" that refers to the entire plant usually cultivated for its blooms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flower

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a flower type to its color. For example, (biology.bloom.color "Rose" "Red") and (biology.bloom.color "Violet" "Blue"). Note that a flower may have more than one color associated with the plant's blooms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Color

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Value type representing the average height for a domesticated breed. Properties within this value type hold data for the breed's minimum and maximum average heights, the unit of height, and the gender and breed for this data.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Average Height

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a breed's average height entity to the breed the fact holds true for.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an average height entity to the gender of the breed the average height applies to. Since male and female genders of the same breed may have statistically different height averages, this property allows the representation of those different facts. For example, if the average height of female Basset Hound is 28???36 cm, the gender in this fact is female.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gender

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a breed's average wheight entity to the average height. For example, if the average height of female Basset Hound is 28???36 cm, the minimum value is 28 and the maximum value is 36.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Height

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Value type representing the average weight for a domesticated breed. Properties within this value type hold data for the breed's minimum and maximum average weights, the unit of weight, and the gender and breed for this data.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Average Weight

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a breed's average weight entity to the breed the fact holds true for. For example, for the fact the average weight of male Scottish Terriers is 8.5 to 10 kg, the breed is Scottish Terrier.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a breed's average weight value type to the gender this average weight fact applies to. For example, for male Scottish Terriers, their average weight is 8.5 to 10 kg, while for female Scottish Terriers, their average weight is 8 to 9.5 kg.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gender

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a breed's average weight entity to the average weight. For the fact, the average weight of male Scottish Terriers is 8.5 to 10 kg, the minimum weight is 8.5, and the maximum is 10.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Weight

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all breed groups. These are the groupings of related breeds of animal by an overseer organization, used to organize the showing of animals.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breed Group

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The registry or other organization that classifies breeds using this group. Each group can belong to only one organization, even if multiple organizations use similar names.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breed registry

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:biology.breed_group to the mso:biology.breed_registration relationship that collects the data about the breed and its inclusion in the breed group for a given organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breeds
Breed origin
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: Use location.location or one of its subclasses instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\jcoop] Successor:[mso:location.location]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Breeds of domesticated animals that originated here.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breeds orginating here
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If needed, we can add a property to location.location. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship type collecting the data on a breed's inclusion in a breed group, including the to and from dates.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breed Registration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:biology.breed_registration relationship to the mso:biology.animal_breed included in the group for the given time period.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.breed_registration relationship to the mso:biology.breed_group the breed is included in for the given time period.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breed Group

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.breed_registration relationship to the date the breed is officially recognized as part of the breed group.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.breed_registration relationship to the date the breed officially ceased to be included in this breed group.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity type representing the collection of all breed registries. These are the organizations that maintain a list of pure-bred animals and are the governing organizations for the recognized breeds and breed groups.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breed Registry

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:biology.breed_registry to the mso:biology.breed_group the registry recognizes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breed Groups

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.breed_registry to an mso:biology.breed_registration relationship that collects the data on a breed and its inclusion in a group that is recognized by the registry.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recognized Breed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all chromosomes. These are the threadlike strands of DNA in a cell nucleus that carries the genes in a linear order.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Chromosome

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.chromosome to the mso:biology.cytogenetic_band(s) located on the chromosome. Bands are the locations on the chromosome that are visible when stained and viewed under a microscope.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Band

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:biology.chromosome to the mso:biology.gene(s) located on the chromosome.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gene

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:biology.chromosome to the mso:biology.genome, the entire set of genetic material for an organism type. For example, the human chromosome 11 is part of the human genome.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Genome

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.chromosome to its mso:biology.genomic_locus, which is a very specific location on the chromosome.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locus

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.chromosome to its identifier. For example, chromosome 5 has an identifier of '5'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Identifier

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all clusters of orthologous groups. These are groups of three or more proteins that are considered orthologs. Orthologs are direct evolutionary counterparts.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cluster of Orthologous Groups

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.cluster_orthologous_group to its mso:biology.biological_function.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Function

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.cluster_orthologous_group to the set of mso:biology.gene(s) that are a part of this cluster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gene

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all colors that can be used to described an animal's coat.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Coat Color

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An enumeration type that indicates whether the organism classification is extant and, if so, how likely it is to become extinct in the near future.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Critically Endangered

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of cryptids. Cryptids are the organisms that are suspected to exist, but have not definitely accepted as documented by the scientific community. Well known examples include the Loch Ness Monster and Momo the Monster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cryptid

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.cryptid to the known biology.organism_classification which may be mistaken as the cryptid. For example, the Plesiosaurus is a known organism that may be mistaken for the Loch Ness Monster.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Alternative Organism

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of cryptid classifications. These are the broad classifications of cryptids, similar to taxonomic groupings. This set includes unproven types like 'lake monster' and groupings with proven types, like 'whales'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cryptid Classification

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all cytogenetic bands. These are the locations on chromosomes that are visible under a microscope when stained.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cytogenetic Band

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.cytogenetic_band to the mso:biology.chromosome on which it is found.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Chromosome

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.cytogenetic_band to its related mso:biology.genomic_locus. Bands narrow the region on a chromosome on which a locus is located.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locus

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.cytogenetic_band to its identifier. For example, the human band 9p11.2 has an identifier of '9p11.2'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Identifier

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all deceased organisms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Deceased Organism

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.deceased_organism to its date of death.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date of Death

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.deceased_organism to its place of death.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Place of Death

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all diet types in biology. This collection includes carnivore, omnivore, and herbivore.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Diet

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collections of all domesticated animals. This collection includes the set of domesticated dogs and domesticated sheep, for example. Domestication is the process by which a population of organisms are genetically changed by selective breeding for the benefit of people.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Domesticated animal

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:biology.domesticated_animal type to the mso:biology.animal_breed(s) that are breeds of this animal type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breeds

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all enzymes. Enzymes are the large biological molecules that are catalysts for thousands of metabolic processes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Enzyme

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.enzyme to its EC number, which is the classification of the enzyme developed by the IUBMB Enzyme Nomenclature authority.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: EC Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all flowering plants. Flowering plants are the diverse grouping of plants whose characteristics include flowers, endosperm within seeds, and production of fruits containing seeds.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flowering Plants

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.flowering_plants entity to the mso:visual_art.color of its blooms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flower Color

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all fossil sites. These are the locations that have had discoveries of fossils, the excavated remains of past organisms.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fossil Site

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.fossil_site to the mso:biology.organism_classification(s) that have been found at this site.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organism Types

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:biology.fossil_site to the specific mso:biology.fossil_specimen(s) found at this site.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Specimens

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all fossil specimens. These are the instances of fossils found. Fossils are the remains of organisms that existed in a past geological age and that has been excavated for study or display.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fossil Specimen

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.fossil_specimen to the date the biological specimen was discovered.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Discovered

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.fossil_specimen to the mso:time.geologic_time_period from which the fossil has been dated.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Geologic Period

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.fossil_specimen to the mso:people.person(s) who discovered the specimen.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Discovered by

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.fossil_specimen to the mso:biology.fossil_site at which the specimen was found.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Site

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.fossil_specimen to its mso:biology.organism_classification.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organism

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all genes. Genes are units of inheritance; more formally, they are locatable regions of genomic sequences that are associated with regulatory regions, transcribed regions, and or other functional sequence regions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gene

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.gene to the mso:biology.chromosome in which it is located.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Chromosome

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.gene to the mso:biology.gene_group_membership relationship that collects data for the gene's inclusion in a gene group.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Membership

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.gene to its mso:biology.genome.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Genome

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology gene to its mso:biology.genomic_locus, the subregion on the chromosome associated with the gene.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Locus

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.gene to its ID as assigned by the National Center for Biotechnology Information.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: NCBI ID

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.gene to the string symbol of the gene. Note this property is not redundant with the name properties on type.object, since those are text properties.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Symbol

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all gene groups. These are the sets of genes grouped by common characteristics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gene Group

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:biology.gene_group to the mso:biology.gene_group_membership relationship that collects the data for a given gene's inclusion to this group.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
An organism classification is a set of living things (e.g., plants, animals, microorganisms) that has a classification rank (e.g., Kingdom, Phylum, Class, Order, Family, Genus, Species, Subspecies). A complete list of possible classifications can be found in the type mso:biology.organism_classification_rank. Note that mso:biology.organism_classification includes scientific types like 'Tilia americana' and 'Panthera tigris', as well as non-scientific types like 'oak' and 'panther'. However, the type mso:biology.organism should be used for individual organisms, such as household pets, animal performers, racehorses, and named plants.
For example, for Labrador Retriever, the classification would break down as follows:
Domain Eukarya Kingdom Animalia Phylum Chordata Class Mammalia Order Carnivora Family Canidae Genus Canis Species Canis lupus Subspecies Canis lupus familiaris Breed Labrador Retriever
Each of these classifications, from the highest (Domain) down to the lowest (Subspecies/Breed/Hybrid /etc.), are all organism classifications.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organism Classification

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.organism_classification to the mso:event.agent that is credited with developing this classification. For example, a person or group is attributed with creating a new organism type, like a new type of rose or new animal breed, like the Jack Russell terriers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Breeder

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:biology.organism_classification to its mso: biology.organism_characteristic, like 'flightless' or 'thorns'
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Characteristics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
Proteins are complex organic compounds that consist of one or more chains of amino acids. They are essential components of any living cell and indispensable to the proper functioning of all organisms.
Things that are Proteins:
## Scleroproteins or fibrous proteins: cytoskeletal proteins (e.g. Keratin 4, Myo1b) and extracellular matrix proteins (e.g Vinculin).
## Globular proteins: plasma proteins (e.g. Human serum albumin, Clusterin), hemoproteins (e.g. Cytochrome, Hemoglobin), cell adhesion proteins (e.g. Laminin, CDH1), proteins that bind with hormones and growth factors (e.g. Insulin-like growth factor binding protein), protein receptors either transmembrane or intracellular (e.g. Glycoprotein, Coup TFII), DNA-binding protein/nuclear proteins (e.g. Histone, Atoh1, Tata binding protein), proteins that aid in nutrient storage and transport (e.g. Ferritin), chaperone proteins (e.g. Calreticulin, heat shock protein 47), and immune system proteins such as antigens and antibodies (e.g. Carcinoembryonic antigen, Immunoglobulin E).
## Membrane proteins (e.g. Glycophorin, CD36).
## Enzymes (e.g. Urease, DNA polymerase).
Things that are NOT Proteins:
## Amino acids (e.g. Lysine, Cysteine) Use mso:biology.amino_acid for these.
## Vitamins and essential nutrients (e.g. Vitamin C, Folic acid). Use mso:chemistry.chemical_compound for these.
## Genes (e.g. Active BCR related gene, Fibrillin 1) Use mso:biology.gene for these.
## Families or groups of proteins (e.g. Ankyrin, Keratin, Karyopherin).
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Protein
